e social silencing of torture and torturous violence specifically. It invites us to consider alternative ways to understand and address the impacts of physical, sexualised and psychological abuses.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aTorturexLaw and legislation. 0aTorturexPrevention. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z97831111967940 cprintz978152921843540uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781529218459?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781529218459423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781529218459/original  a978-3-11-119679-4  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles